ST Engineering-NTU Corporate Lab  invites applications for the position of Research Associate. 
Key Responsibilities:

  Develop and design intelligent perception and localization algorithms for autonomous sweeper in urban environments
  Implement algorithms on real platform and conduct outdoor testing

Job Requirements:

  Master's degree in Electrical and Electronic Engineering, or in a field related to vision Lidar based navigation, SLAM, and 3D mapping
  Background in intelligence perception and autonomous robotics for a project aimed at urban environment autonomous sweeper localization
  Experience of working with mobile robotic sensors and systems
  Good verbal and written communication skills in English
  Highly self-motivated, creative thinking, hands-on skills, team work and interpersonal skills

We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.